Description: When the user receives a turn while under Reading, slightly decrease all enemies' buff effects and slightly increase all enemies' debuff effects. (Changes [de]buffs by 10% of current value, rounded down)

Name: Sugari no Ontachi Ornament
Description: When the user receives a turn while under Reading, slightly increase all allies' buff effects and slightly decrease all allies' debuff effects. (Changes [de]buffs by 10% of current value, rounded down)

Name: Crossovered Endangered Bird
Description: When the user is at the front while under Reading, slightly increase effects of PSN's HP Drain (~12% more damage), HVY's DEF and SPD debuff (-60% DEF and -18% SPD), TRR's all stat debuff (-13.5% to all stats) and SIL's MND and MAG debuff (-60% MND and -25% MAG) on enemies.

Name: An Eye for An Eye
Description: When Tokiko takes damage from an enemy's attack, she receives a (SLv * 5) buff to her Attack.

Name: Love the Way You Read
Description: The user's appropriate spell cards have increased chances of giving the Reading status.

Name: Tokiko's Thick Book CQC
Description: If the skill holder is under the effect of "Reading", increase DEF and MND by 25%. If the skill holder is not under the effect of "Reading", increase ATK and MAG by 25%.

Name: Bookworm Youkai's Ardor
Description: When the skill holder is under the effect of "Reading", "The Count of Monte Cristo" and "Musketeer d'Artagnan"'s special effects are further strengthened, and the spells' power is also increased. When this effect activates, there is a low chance that "Reading" effect will disappear.

Name: Bookworm Youkai's Grudge
Description: In battle, if Reimu or Marisa is in the back, "Reimu & Marisa's Abuse Victim" will activate at half strength.

Name: MP Boost
Description: Increases MP.

Name: Evasion Boost
Description: Increases Evasion.

Name: Motivated Heart
Description: Skill holder receives (SLv * 6)% more experience. Only takes effect when in party (active or reserve). Does not stack with "Hands-on Experience", but does stack with all other modifying skills.

Name: Hands-on Experience
Description: Skill holder receives (SLv * 12)% more experience. Only takes effect when in active party at end of battle. Does not stack with "Motivated Heart", but does stack with all other modifying skills.

Name: Earth Spirits Palace Party
Description: While the user is on the front line, if Utsuho, Rin and/or Satori are on the front line, the user's stats will be increased by (SLv * 8) % per members on the front line, excluding themselves. This can only takes effect if at least one ally or enemy has performed an action in the battle.

Name: Myouren Temple Disciple?
Description: If the user receives a turn while Byakuren is in the front, copy 1/3 of Byakuren's stat buffs. (Only if the user's current buff is lower)

Name: Super-Responsive Senses
Description: When the user evades an attack, increase ATB by 3000.

Name: Subconscious Manipulation
Description: When an enemy is using an attack that targets all party members, increase the user's DEF, MND and Evasion by (SLv * 8)%. (This is only factored per attack, and is not a persistent buff)

Name: Subconscious Genetics
Description: When the user fails to evade an attack, increase Subconscious Genetics counter by 1. The user's evasion is increased by (counter * 10)%. When the user successfully evades an attack, remove the counter. (doesn't get any benefit from SLv)

Name: Expansion of Consciousness
Description: Increase MP Recovery Rate by (SLv * 1).

Name: Embryo's Dream
Description: When the user evades an attack, there's a 33% chance of increasing the "Embryo's Dream" counter by 1 (the counter maxes at 5). When attacking, using a spell, or using Concentrate while Embryo's Dream counter is present, reduce the counter by 1 and repeat the action. This will use MP as normal, and won't activate if the user doesn't have enough MP.

Name: Super-responsive Senses+
Description: When Super-responsive Senses activate, action gauge is increased by 10000 instead.

Name: Embryo, Why Do You Dance?
Description: When evading an attack, the chance of "Embryo's Dream" counter increasing is doubled.

Name: HP Boost
Description: Increases HP.

Name: MP Boost
Description: Increases MP.

Name: TP Boost
Description: Increases TP.

Name: Motivated Heart
Description: Skill holder receives (SLv * 6)% more experience. Only takes effect when in party (active or reserve). Does not stack with "Hands-on Experience", but does stack with all other modifying skills.

Name: Hands-on Experience
Description: Skill holder receives (SLv * 12)% more experience. Only takes effect when in active party at end of battle. Does not stack with "Motivated Heart", but does stack with all other modifying skills.

Name: Hyperthymestic Memory
Description: If the user is in the party, the "View Ally/Enemy Information" menu will display enemies' current HP.

Name: Gensokyo Chronicles Wisdom
Description: When the user is in front, all frontliners inflict 16% more damage when targeting a weakness.

Name: Memories of Gensokyo
Description: When the user takes a turn, remove one negative status ailment or debuff from all frontliners. Ailments will be prioritized over stat debuffs.

Name: Miare Descendant's Power
Description: If the user's HP becomes 0 while having at least 1 TP, there is a (SLv * 9)% chance to consume 15 TP to fully restore HP. This effect does not activate if the user doesn't have enough TP.

Name: Ultra Incantation
Description: After using Concentrate, the next action's damage or healing will be multiplied by (1.8 + SLv * 0.3).

Name: Phenomenal Force of Will
Description: When the user receives a turn, restore 1 MP.

Name: In Search of More Wisdom
Description: Occasionally "Wise Protection Art" and "Wise Defensive Art" will affect all frontliners.

Name: Protector of Knowledge
Description: "Invincibility" and "Immunity" will naturally disappear half as often.

Name: True Maiden of Miare
Description: "Miare Descendant's Power" will occasionally not consume TP when it activates.
